title: zuo_le_(arknights)
body: [i]Zuo Le, of the Sui Regulator of Great Yan, there to mind your safety even when it's not his job.[/i] A playable Guard Operator in [[Arknights]]. A Candleholder of Yan, tasked with keeping [[Nian (arknights)|]] and her many siblings in check. He first made an appearance in the Sui saga as an NPC, before being introduced as an operator during the side story [i]Here a People Sows[/i]. His motif is based on the spiny bush viper and the mythological Tengshe. His [[voice actor]]s are Toyonaga Toshiyuki (Japanese), Li Jiaxiang (Chinese and Henanese), Vincent Tong (English) and Kim Da-ol (Korean). His art designer is [[Jiuri Jiuhao]]. h4. title: willis_tower
body: Formerly known as the Sears Tower, the Willis Tower is a 444.3 meter (1,451-foot) tall skyscraper located in the Loop area of [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], the [[United States]]. The skyscraper was built from 1970 to 1974, and held the title of tallest building from 1973 to 1998, when it was surpassed by the [[Petronas Twin Towers]].

title: alcatraz
body: United States Penitentiary, Alcatraz Island or simply Alcatraz (literally meaning the Gannet in Spanish) was an infamous [[prison]] located on Alcatraz Island,  [[San Francisco]] Bay, [[California]], the [[United States]]. Originally built as a military prison, Alcatraz would later serve as a maximum security federal prison from 1933-1963. The former prison would be widely known for the escape attempt in the summer of 1962 before its full closure.

title: jessica_(arknights)
body:
[i]Jessica, Sniper Operator of Blacksteel, will provide effective attack power for the squad with her professional skills.[/i]

A playable Sniper Operator in [[Arknights]]. Real Name: [Spoiler]Jessica Brynley[/spoiler].

A fully enlisted Operator from [[Blacksteel Worldwide (arknights)|]] (BSW), stationed at Rhodes Island as part of an exchange training program. Very timid and insecure but reliable and trustworthy, as noted by other Operators, especially with equipment testing. Holds her BSW seniors [[Franka (arknights)|]] and [[Liskarm (arknights)|]] in high regard.

Heavily implied to be extremely wealthy, particularly due to her acquiring Laterano firearms which costs a huge fortune, amassing large amounts of ammunition by "cutting down on food expense", and her interaction with [[Snowsant (arknights)|]].

Her [[voice actor]] is [[Hirohashi Ryou]].

title: bully_maguire_(meme)
body: Bully Maguire is a meme based on scenes of [[Tobey Maguire]] as [[Peter Parker]] after he's combined with the symbiote Venom in Sam Raimi's [[Spider-Man 3]]. In the film, Parker becomes hot-headed and arrogant after combining with Venom, causing him to treat others poorly. This version of Parker has been dubbed Emo Peter Parker by many across the web, with Bully Maguire acting as an alternative to this title. In Bully Maguire videos, scenes featuring Parker in this symbiote-driven state are edited and remixed into new scenarios to make it seem like Maguire is bullying other characters, typically from the Marvel Cinematic Universe.

title: evil_eye_(dandadan)
body:
The Evil Eye is a yokai who has spent years bound to the Tsuchinoko sacrificial house and is known for cursing humans to commit suicide with his gaze. After possessing [[Enjoji Jin]], the Evil Eye makes it his goal to kill all humans he comes across, however, after becoming friends with [[Takakura Ken (Dandadan)|]], the Evil Eye makes a deal with him to only target him through an exchange of fights.

In [[Dandadan]], the Evil Eye serves as the tertiary antagonist during the Cursed House Arc and the main antagonist in the Evil Eye Arc.

title: opfor_(call_of_duty)
body:
A paramilitary faction led by [[Khaled al-Asad]]. [b]OpFor[/b] is short for Opposing Forces or Opposition Force. 

In [[Call of Duty 4]], they took power in an unnamed Middle Eastern country in 2011 following an armed coup. The Russian [[Ultranationalists (Call of Duty)|]] supply [[weapon]]s to the OpFor for being their ally. 

In [[Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2|Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2 (2009)]], the OpFor appears in [[Afghanistan]]. The fighters are seen wearing [[camouflage]] [[military fatigues]].

title: the_two-thousand_yard_stare
body:
[b]The 2000 Yard Stare[/b] is a painting by [[World War II]] war correspondent "Thomas Calloway Lea III":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_C._Lea_III] who had traveled extensively in the Pacific theater. 

The painting depicts a nameless [[united states marine corps|U.S. Marine]] at the [[Battle of Peleliu]] with the eponymous stare. The marine is seen wearing [[military fatigues]] with his [[open jacket|jacket open]] and a [[torn clothes|tear]] [[torn jacket|on the left shoulder]], his [[combat helmet|helmet]] [[dent]]ed and [[tilted headwear|askew]]. In the background is a war-torn landscape, other marines, a [[tank]] and three [[airplane|planes]].

The phrase "[[thousand yard stare]]" was popularized after the painting was published in [i]Life[/i] magazine, though it was not referred to with that title in the 1945 article.

* !asset #13755782: Original painting

h4. See also

* [[sanpaku]]
* [[thousand yard stare]]

* "Wikipedia: Thousand-yard stare":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thousand-yard_stare

body:
An android representing the [[De Lisle carbine]] [[sniper rifle]] in [[Girls' Frontline]].

A willful T-Doll who likes collecting in-ear headphones. She would try out new products at stereo stores and post detailed reviews on different models on the forum. She is therefore hailed as the headphone guru on the forum, but she has no patience when it comes to giving people headphone recommendations. Since her hobby can be quite expensive, she is always complaining about her bonus being too small.

title: m99_(girls'_frontline)
body:
A character from [[Girls' Frontline]] representing the [[Zijiang M99]], frequently confused with the Barrett M99 due to similarities with their name.

Shortest of all Sniper Rifle wielding users, she has [[short hair|short]], [[black hair]] with a big red ribbon as well as a stuffed rabbit carrying a grenade. She has red eyes.

She wears a sleeveless white shirt with a red necktie, a red skirt with star pattern that references the Chinese national flag. The triple-bar shoulder badge refers to the battalion leader of Young Pioneers of China in Chinese elementary school. She wears [[bike shorts]] underneath as well as carrying a rabbit-like backpack.

Due to her appearance as a child, she is good at learning new things as well as a role model of good manners, however she's also very aggressive and sometimes she's stubborn due to her less social experience, plus she is extremely cautious about her pride and appearance, which would often lead her to funny and annoying situations.

h4. Appearance

title: big_smoke's_order_(meme)
body:
[i]"I’ll have two number 9s, a number 9 large, a number 6 with extra dip, a number 7, two number 45s, one with cheese, and a large soda."[/i]

A [[meme]] originated from a cutscene in the mission "Drive-Thru":[https://gta.fandom.com/wiki/Drive-Thru] from [[Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas]].

The scene involves [[Carl Johnson|CJ]] and his fellow gang members [[Sweet (grand theft auto)|]], [[Ryder (grand theft auto)|]], and [[Big Smoke]] ordering [[fast food]] at the [[drive-thru]] of Cluckin' Bell. After his gang mates placed their order, Smoke then proceeds to make an extremely large order that later became a subject of parody and meme.

h4. External links
* Know Your Meme: "Big Smoke's Order":[https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/big-smokes-order]

title: sterling_(girls'_frontline)
body:
An android representing the [[Sterling SMG]] [[submachine gun]] in [[Girls' Frontline]].

A self-important Doll with a bit of an 8th Grade Syndrome who believes she's the Chosen One and takes great pride in that. No matter how daunting a mission is, she will never admit defeat, especially when STEN is around. A rampaging fighter who does not hold back on the battlefield, she would sometimes do dangerous things like venturing deep behind enemy lines alone, though she is always incredibly lucky and would make it back safe and sound. All in all, she is a great teammate that would rather risk her own life than put her friends in danger. On an unrelated note, for some reason, she does not work well with left-handers at all.

h4. Appearance

title: vigneron_m2_(girls'_frontline)
body:
An android representing the [[vigneron submachine gun|Vigneron M2]] [[submachine gun]] in [[Girls' Frontline]].

She has [[purple eyes]] and [[brown hair|brown]] [[long hair]].
Her default skin outfit consists of a [[black headwear|black]] [[beret]], [[goggles]], [[black sports bra]], [[grey belt]] with [[belt pouch|pouches]], [[black pants]] and [[cross-laced footwear|cross-laced]] [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]].

A Doll who loves making mechanical modifications. As a pragmatist who pursues pragmatism in all things, she dislikes impractical designs that only look new and flashy and likes to modify everything she sees. She claims to despise garage kits and thinks that when it comes to things like cars and planes, only the real deal is worth the time. However, since acquiring the actual items is too much trouble, she secretly creates garage kits using metal.

Illustrated by [[Bobo (6630978)|]]. 

h4. Appearance

* !post #4968116

title: cx4_storm_(girls'_frontline)
body:
An android representing the Italian-made [[Beretta Cx4|Beretta Cx4 Storm]] [[bullpup]] carbine in the game [[Girls' Frontline]].

Cx4 is a cheerful-looking girl with [[very long hair|very long]] [[black hair]] tied back with [[large bow|large]] [[red bow|red]] [[hair bow]], [[parted bangs]], wide [[red eyes]], a single exposed [[fang]], and [[medium breasts]]. 

The upper half of her outfit consists of a [[black choker]], a red bow pinned with a [[blue gemstone|sapphire]] [[brooch]], a [[black jacket|black]] [[shrug (clothing)|shrug]] with white [[wrist cuffs]], a short, [[white shirt|white]], [[buttons|button-up]] [[crop top]] fastened down with a [[belt]], plenty of [[navel|exposed]] [[midriff]], and of course, her namesake [[gun]].

From the waist down, it's made up of a pair of hip [[strap]]s that hold up a white [[pelvic curtain]], two criss-crossing [[belt]]s with an attached [[belt pouch]], a black bikini bottom, [[garter straps]] that attach to [[black thighhighs|black]] sawtooth-trimmed [[thighhighs]], a pair of [[thigh strap]]s, and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[leather boots|leather]] [[knee boots]].

title: fuchikoma
body:
The [[robot|AI-controlled]] [[walker (robot)|spider]] [[tank]]s from the original [[Ghost in the Shell]] manga. Because of a trademark claim arising from the Ghost in the Shell Playstation game, Fuchikomas couldn't be used in the [[Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex]] TV series, so they were redesigned and renamed as [[Tachikoma]]s.

Also see [[Logicoma]] (from [[Ghost in the Shell Arise]]) and [[Gertsecomma]] (from [[Koukaku no Pandora]]).

title: kurobe_natsumi
body:
Secondary character of [[Senpai ga Uzai Kouhai no Hanashi]], a childhood friend of [[Igarashi Futaba]].

A woman that gives off "sexy vixen" vibes: attractive, cunning, has experience in love relationships, all that being used throughout the series to troll Futaba. Often hits the mark, despite Futaba's reactions.

[i]Appearance:[/i] [[short_hair|Short]] [[black hair]], often wear black clothes. Sometimes gets darker tint of skin tone than "average" character. [[yellow_eyes|Amber eyes]] with noticeably [[slit pupils]], usually wear [[triangle_earrings|triangle/pyramid earrings]] with matching color. Approx. C-cup.

Associated color: Amber

title: igarashi_futaba
body:
Main character of [[Senpai ga Uzai Kouhai no Hanashi]], the "kouhai" of the story.

A girl being short by stature and temper. Works as [[office_lady|a clerk at office]]. While she's easy to set off, Futaba has her cute and kind side which are being covered by her thick "[[tsundere]] hide", especially towards her senior, [[Takeda Harumi]]. Due to her appearance, she's often being confused as a middle-school student or someone's daughter. Skilled at cooking, particularly around home-style meals.


[i]Appearance:[/i] While other characters have normal proportions, she has rather "chibi" vibes - short stature, rounded wide face, shoulder wide head. [[Medium hair|Medium length hair]] tied in [[ponytail]] and chin-long [[sidelocks]]. [[green_hair|Hair]] and [[green_eyes|iris]] colored in sage green shade. Often seen with a [[fang]] and getting out her [[sharp teeth]] when annoyed. Futaba may be a girl of [[petite]] body but her claws are sharp and able to deliver quite a painful beating.

Associated color: sage green
Associated animal: cat

title: sakurai_touko
body:
Main/supporting character of [[Senpai ga Uzai Kouhai no Hanashi]]. A senior in [[takeda harumi|Harumi]] and [[igarashi futaba|Futaba]]'s company.

A coquettish woman who tends to act as a Greek chorus of sorts, stated to be "popular with men" in the workplace and a low-key source of envy for [[Igarashi Futaba]] on occasion. Pleasant and cheerful, she tends to act without thinking and loves to tease her juniors - a trait shared by her companion [[Kazama Souta]]. She does, however, care for and monitor her coworkers, generally picking up on Igarashi's bad moods quickly and displaying concern. Sometimes she is the cause of some funny situations.

She tends to dress in fairly conservative clothing, sticking with a [[shirt]] and [[pants]] combo, perhaps with a [[sweater]] in colder times. She has [[black hair|black]] [[medium hair|shoulder-length hair]] and [[sidelocks]], [[black eyes]], and a [[mole under eye|mole under her right eye]]. Her [[large breasts]] are occasionally commented on by other characters in-story. Solid D-cup.

Associated color: "Melon orange":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shades_of_orange#Melon

title: takeda_harumi
body:
Main character of [[Senpai ga Uzai Kouhai no Hanashi]], the "Senpai" of the story. 

A big guy with a big mouth and a big heart. A man with an imposing physique - while he is no taller than one head, he is almost double as wide as any average character and possesses physical strength matching his body. He is brutally honest, speaking his thoughts and opinion aloud and in anyone's face. Harumi is a strong extrovert, often seeking a company to hang out, never being shy around people, and has a loud laugh. He takes great care towards his junior, [[Igarashi Futaba]], and has a "tidal lock" sync with her, meaning he has a high chance to encounter her in random places.

While he is very sociable, he is oblivious to current social standards and trends. He often get punched by Futaba for his brutal honesty or saying too much. It's just his head is that thick. 

Associated color: "'Pomp and power'":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shades_of_purple#Pomp_and_Power purple
Associated animal: bear

title: katagiri_sanae
body:
A 28 year old [[policewoman]] [[idol]] from [[Idolmaster Cinderella Girls]]. She has [[large breasts]] and [[brown hair]] usually in [[short twintails|short]], [[low twintails]]. 

Sanae is a former police officer who quit the force to become an idol, largely because the Producer convinced her. She is very flirtatious to the Producer and uses a lot of police terminology when talking. She wishes to be seen by other idols as an older sister and be called Onee-sama, despite the fact that she is shorter than idols who are half her age. Sanae has a black belt in Aikido, Judo, and Karate. She also tends to get upset if others mention that she is single, and is very easily susceptible to drinking to drown her sorrows.

She is in the upper tier for bust size, which is further enhanced because she's rather short. Her cards often reference that she wants to put the Producer in handcuffs, lock him up, and do an interrogation as a teasing double entendre.

In the tie in Cinderella Girls Theater skits, Sanae is a former police officer. She sees herself as an older sister to her fellow idols and will go to great lengths to help promote this. She leads training lessons for [[Aino Nagisa]], [[Akanishi Erika]], [[Yagami Makino]], and [[Ohnishi Yuriko]]. While she finds it extremely difficult, Sanae continues to do so because she wants to be considered reliable. She puts other’s wants before hers, and can sometimes wind up looking like a fool because of it. She is nervous when it comes to [[Aihara Yukino]]’s high class tea and ceramics.

Sanae has a habit of getting drunk, and often drags other idols into it as well. She has found drinking buddies in [[Takagaki Kaede]], [[Hiiragi Shino]], [[Shinohara Rei]], and [[Hyodo Rena]] and made friends with [[Yanagi Kiyora]]. Sanae earned a movie role of an evil mahjong player, and in turn became one of [[Munakata Atsumi]]’s ogling victims. Her sense of style seems to mostly include extremely short dresses that show a lot of cleavage. She is said to be stunning in a bathing suit, although she has put on a child’s swimsuit in order to gain attention.

Due to her popularity, she was selected for the 8th CINDERELLA MASTER CD series, alongside [[Tachibana Arisu]], [[Ichinose Shiki]], [[Shiomi Syuko]], and [[Sakurai Momoka]]. She is voiced by [[Waki Azumi]] [和氣 あず未].

title: wonder_woman
body:
A [[DC Comics]] superheroine with superpowers very similar to those of [[Superman]] (superstrength, superhuman durability, flight, etc.), but without his weakness to Kryptonite.

Also known as [b]Princess Diana of Themyscira[/b]. She is the Amazonian princess and a daughter of Hyppolita. Her notable weapons including her bracers and her [[Lasso of Truth]]. 

She was created by the late William Moulton Marston and the late Harry G. Peter and was first introduced in [i]All-Star Comics[/i] #8 (1942).

title: zb-26
body:
The [b]ZB-26[/b] or ZB vz. 26 (incorrect nomenclature) is a gas-operated, Czechoslovak [[light machine gun]], chambered for the 7.92x57mm Mauser cartridge. Developed in the 1920s, designed by Václav Holek, and mainly manufactured by Zbrojovka Brno, it saw major use during [[World War II]] by several [[military|militaries]]. The design of the ZB-26 heavily influenced the British [[Bren LMG]], as well as the Japanese [[type 96 light machine gun|Type 96]] and [[type 99 light machine gun|Type 99]] light machine guns.

title: boys_anti_tank_rifle
body:
The [b]Boys Anti-tank Rifle[/b] is a British .55 caliber anti-tank [[rifle]], developed shortly before the outbreak of [[World War II]], for the purpose of allowing infantry to fight against enemy armored threats. As with all anti-tank rifles, the Boys was not necessarily meant to destroy the [[tank]] outright, but to inflict a mobility kill by destroying the tank's tracks, or to kill the tank's crew by firing through the armor or vision slits. 

Though the Boys was reasonably effective at the start of the war, the rapid pace of tank development through World War II quickly outstripped the Boys' effectiveness; worse, for anything the Boys [i]could[/i] still damage, so too would the [[Browning M2]], which the British had in ever more plentiful supply and which were useful in several other roles that the Boys was not. By 1943, the Boys was withdrawn from frontline service, replaced by the [[PIAT]].

In anime, the Boys Anti-tank Rifle is famously used by [[Lynette Bishop]] in [[Strike Witches]], as well as [[karin (blue archive)|Karin]] in [[Blue Archive]].

h4. See also

* [[anti-materiel rifle]]
* [[List of weapons]]

title: m1918_bar
body:
The [b]M1918 Browning Automatic Rifle[/b] (BAR) is an American select-fire rifle chambered for .30-06 Springfield cartridge and designed by [[john moses browning|John Browning]] in 1917 for the American Expeditionary Forces in Europe as a replacement for the [[Chauchat]]. Though it is technically [i]not[/i] a [[light machine gun]], the BAR was frequently issued and used in that role, and as such is recognized as one today. The [[weapon]] is recognizable by its straight 20-round magazine, rectangular one-piece forearm, and a [[flip-up sight|flip-up rear sight]] with a windage knob.

This tag also applies to any foreign-produced variants, such as the Polish [b]Browning wz. 28[/b] which notably has a pistol grip (post #6539181) or the French [b]MAS mle 1922[/b].
In anime the BAR is best known for its usage by [[Charlotte E. Yeager]] from [[Strike Witches]].

h4. See also

title: the_grand_tour
body:
The spiritual successor to the [[BBC (broadcaster)|BBC]]'s popular motoring show [[Top Gear]], created by [[Amazon (company)|]] after [[Jeremy Clarkson]] was fired from the BBC for punching a producer. The structure is more or less the same as Top Gear, featuring car reviews, road trips, creation challenges, talk show segments, and celebrity guests (before season 3), albeit with a higher budget than Top Gear. The show features the same trio of hosts, referred to as the "holy trinity" by some.

However, after season 3, the show switched its format, and started doing specials only, up until season 6; with the final special, "[i]One for the Road[/i]", marking the end of the 22 year-long partnership of the original presenters.

title: money_gun
body:
A [[gun]]-shaped novelty device designed to shoot out paper money.  Also called a [i]cash cannon[/i].  A common version of the device is a boxy gun-shaped device where a stack of bills are loaded into the top and its lid helps to hold down the stack of bills.  With the pull of the trigger a wheel inside touching the lowest bill in the stack will rapidly spin and propel the bill through the slot in the front.  It can readily be used to make [[falling money]].

Money guns appear as a weapon used in Osaka in the series [[Kill la Kill]].

title: wasp_(marvel)
body: Character from [[marvel|Marvel Comics]], real name ([[Janet van Dyne]]). She has the power to shrink to a height of several centimeters, fly via insectoid wings, and fire energy blasts. She is a founding member of [[avengers (series)|the Avengers]] and the one who gave them their name as well as a longtime leader of the team. She is also the ex-wife of [[Hank Pym]] and the stepmother of Nadia van Dyne.

title: iron_man
body:
[[marvel|Marvel Comics]] superhero, one of the founding members of the Avengers.

Born [[tony stark|Anthony Edward Stark]], and usually called Tony, he is an industrialist playboy and ingenious engineer who suffers a severe heart injury during a kidnapping in which his captors attempt to force him to build a weapon of mass destruction. He instead creates a powered suit of armor to save his life and escape captivity. He later uses the suit to protect the world as Iron Man. Through his multinational corporation ― Stark Industries ― Tony has created many military weapons, some of which, along with other technological devices of his making, have been integrated into his suit, helping him fight crime.

title: ant-man
body: [[Marvel]] superhero with the power to shrink or enlarge himself, as well control an army of ants. The original Ant-Man was [[Hank Pym]], who would later be succeeded by [[Scott Lang]].

title: mg36_(girls'_frontline)
body:
An android representing the [[H&K MG36]] [[machine gun]] in [[Girls' Frontline]].

She doesn't speak much, but that's not because she's introverted. She's keenly aware of her own worth and is utterly devoted to her employer. It seems she was once involved in some sort of mysterious work in the past and is very reluctant to talk about her past history. However, she visibly relaxes when it comes to discussing sci-fi movies and fiction.

In the prequel spin-off game, [[Girls' Frontline Neural Cloud|Neural Cloud]], MG36 appears as [[Rise (neural cloud)|]]. Voiced by [[Yukana]] and illustrated by [[Funengliang jieheti]].

title: tina_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Tina[/b], known as [b]Rika[/b] (リッカ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [[Pokemon Masters EX]]. Formerly listed as Camilla and Sazanka (サザンカ) in the very first datamines of the game.

She has [[brown eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[orange hair|hair]] with [[swept bangs]]. She wears a [[black hairband|hairband]], a [[black sports bra|sports bra]] under an [[partially unzipped|unzipped]] [[orange jacket|orange]] [[two-tone jacket|and]] [[white jacket|white]] [[track jacket|jacket]] with [[three-quarter sleeves|3/4-length sleeves]], a [[red wristband|band]], [[bike shorts|spats]], a [[bandaid on knee|bandaid]], [[orange footwear|orange]] [[sneakers|shoes]], and a [[white bag|white]] [[shoulder bag|bag]].

She is close friends with [[paulo_(pokemon)|Paulo]], and her partner Pokémon is [[Flareon]].

Voiced by [[Takagaki Ayahi]].

h4. External links

* "Bulbapedia: Tina":[https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Tina]

title: sleeves_rolled_up
body:
When a character wears their clothes with both or one of its sleeves rolled up. This can be either to cool themselves off, to prevent the sleeves from getting dirty or wet, because of clothing regulations (for example [[uniform|uniforms]]), or because of their taste in fashion.

Includes sleeves visibly only folded up once. Not to be confused with [[sleeves pushed up]], in which case the sleeves are only pushed up the arm, instead of being folded up.

h4. See also
* [[three-quarter sleeves]]
* [[tasuki]]

For [[pants]], see [[pants_rolled_up]].

title: hop_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Hop[/b] is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon swsh|Sword and Shield]][/i].

This Trainer from the town of Postwick is Leon’s little brother. His experience in the Gym Challenge inspired him to chase a new dream of becoming a Pokémon Professor [tn](official bio)[/tn]. His first Pokémon was [[Wooloo]].

He has [[dark-skinned male|dark skin]], [[yellow eyes]] with [[white pupils]], and [[short hair|short]] [[purple hair]]. He wears a [[black shirt]] under an [[open jacket|open]] [[blue jacket|blue]] [[fur-trimmed jacket|jacket]] with [[three-quarter sleeves|3/4-length sleeves]], [[black pants]], [[shoes]], and carries a [[green bag|green]] [[duffel bag]].

title: glacia_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Glacia[/b], known as [b]Purim[/b] (プリム) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon rse|Ruby and Sapphire]][/i].

One of the Hoenn League Elite Four, this elegant lady traveled far to hone her Pokémon's Ice-type moves. She seeks opponents with a fiery passion for battle [tn](official bio)[/tn]. 

She has [[pale skin]], [[blue eyes]], and [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] styled in [[quad tails]]. In her [[pokemon oras|ORAS]] outfit, she wears a [[white choker]], a [[low-cut]] [[purple dress]] with [[three-quarter sleeves|three-quarter-length sleeves]], [[white gloves]], and [[blue footwear|blue]] [[high heels]].

title: sleeves_pushed_up
body:
When a character wears his or her clothes with both or one of its sleeves pushed or pulled up. This can be either to cool themselves off, to prevent the sleeves from getting dirty or wet or getting in the way of what they are doing, or simply due to the characters' taste in fashion. They also do this if they are preparing to deliver a blow to someone in a comical way or if they are getting ready for something difficult.

Do not confuse with [[sleeves rolled up]], in which cases the sleeves are carefully folded up the arm, not simply pushed up.

For [[pants]], see [[pants rolled up]].

h4. See also

* [[three-quarter sleeves]]

title: hanabusa_lisa_(3rd_costume)
body:
The third [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[VSPO!]]'s [[Hanabusa Lisa]], as seen in post #5166694.

A non-conventional Chinese-themed outfit.

In this costume, her hair is styled in [[twintails]] with [[double bun]], and the base of the buns is encircled with what appears to be a white [[lace-trimmed hair ornament|lace-trimmed ornaments]] atop her head, tied with [[black ribbon|black]] [[hair ribbon|ribbon]].

For the torso, she wears a set of clothing in [[chinese clothes|Chinese style]] consisting of what appears to be a [[pink shrug|pink]] Chinese-styled [[shrug (clothing)|shrug]] with a high collar similar to [[mandarin collar|mandarin collars]]. The shrug has [[puffy long sleeves|puffy]] [[three-quarter sleeves|elbow length sleeves]] with [[arm_cutout|arm cutouts]] on both sleeves ornamented with a flower-shaped cloth. Under the shrug, she wears a [[cropped_shirt|cropped]] [[white shirt|white]] [[frilled_shirt|frilled]] shirt with a [[see-through_cleavage|see-through cleavage]]. The [[crop_top|cropped]] top hinted a [[midriff_peek|slight midriff]] and ornamented with a [[black ribbon]] from the neck part until the cropped end of her top and to her right thigh and left hip. She also wears a [[lace_gloves|lace]] [[half_gloves|half gloves]]. [s]Alternatively, if these are too much, you can probably just put [[china dress]] and [[pink dress]] and call it a day.[/s]

Below, she wears a [[white skirt|white]] [[miniskirt]] under a [[pink overskirt]] that serves as a [[pelvic curtain]]. She wears [[asymmetrical legwear|asymmetrically styled]] [[white thighhighs]] in which her right thigh-high is connected with an [[o-ring]] to what appears to be a [[single pantsleg]] under the skirt. For shoes, she wears [[black_footwear|black]] [[flats]] with ankle strap.

h4. External links

* "Costume reveal stream":https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yBi-NlPTgaY

title: female_grappler_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon and fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Female Fighter (dungeon and fighter)|]]. Also known as the Dervish or Ultimate Diva.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/2/2b/GrapplerPortrait.png] has her wearing a luchador-esque [[wrestling_outfit|wrestling outfit]] (the mask being in her left hand) with a [[championship_belt|gold-plated trophy belt]] around her waist. Unlike her other forms, her hair is cut [[short_hair|short]] here.

As an "Ultimate Diva":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/6/6c/UltimateDivaPortrait.png], she has [[dark_skin|dark skin]] and swaps out most of her outfit with a white leather bikini top and gauntlets with free-flowing decorative leather straps. Her hair is a more voluminous version of her base class's, with white [[streaked_hair|highlights]] appearing throughout it.

Her "Neo Grappler":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/c/c9/Full_Neo-_Female_Grappler_Artwork_Uncens.png] form features a more extravagant version of the Ultimate Diva's outfit with gold trimmings. She also has a gold lightning bolt [[tattoo]] under her right eye. Accompanying her are two unnamed wrestlers wearing similar outfits - a blonde with a [[bob_cut|bob cut]] and another with long, black hair.

title: ellin_meiji
body:
Commissioner: 명지남편
Romanization: Myeonggihusband

[[original|Original character]] made by 명지남편. He has made dozens of [[commission]]s of her. 

A [[fox girl]] without a tail. She is a [[female fighter (dungeon and fighter)|fighter]] class, [[female striker (dungeon and fighter)|striker]] subclass awakened [[kaiser (dungeon and fighter)|]] character from the game [[dungeon and fighter|Dungeon Fighter Online]].

She has [[blonde hair]] and a [[ponytail]].

title: female_brawler_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon and fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Female Fighter (dungeon and fighter)|]]. Also known as the Hellcat or Black Widow.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/b/bc/BrawlerPortrait.png] is similar to her base class, but with spikier hair and scars covering her body. The brick and gauntlets she wields are coated with a purple poison.

As a "Black Widow":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/5/55/BlackWidowPortrait.png], she wears a black jacket and shorts with orange trimmings, wielding different weapons - a claw, throwing knives, and some throwing needles strapped to her thigh. Her hair is now left free-flowing, becoming a [[hime_cut|hime cut]].

Her appearance as a "Neo Brawler":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/7/79/Full_Neo-_Female_Brawler_Artwork.png] goes for a more punk look, wearing predominantly leather clothing decorated with studs and spikes, with the sole exception being her snakeskin vest.

title: when_he's_copying_your_snaps_so_you_pull_this_move_(meme)
body:
When He's Copying Your Snaps So You Pull This Move or Boom Shakalaka Yess Gawd is a redraw meme trend based on a TikTok slideshow of a girl flexing her muscles so that the boy copying her Snapchat posts will also flex his muscles. The TikTok was originally posted by user @bostynbaker in December 2024 but has since been deleted. That month, a redraw of the slideshow was posted to X / Twitter, inspiring further redraws throughout December 2024 and January 2025.

title: amia_(andromedako_(akiyamamizuki))
body:
[[Andromedako (AkiyamaMizuki)]]'s [[original]] character.

The character has multiple versions that are self-inserts into different series, one being for [[Project Sekai]], and another for [[Limbus Company]] that the author [[oc x canon|yume-ships]] with [[Ishmael (project moon)|]] from the same game.

In both versions, the character has [[pink eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[pink hair]]. The Project Sekai version also has [[green hair|green]] or [[purple hair|purple]] [[streaked hair|streaks]] in their hair and generally has it tied into a [[high ponytail]], while the Limbus Company version wears their hair loose and has darker pink [[colored tips|tips]].

The character's sheet lists their gender as nonbinary (Project Sekai version) or ??? (Limbus Company version), and their pronouns as they/them. As such, their gender should be tagged as [[1other]].

h4. External links
* "Toyhouse - character info (Project Sekai version)":[https://toyhou.se/11697136.amia-sona]
* "Toyhouse - character info (Limbus Company version)":[https://toyhou.se/27055807.amia-lcb-self-insert]

title: katsuragi_(azur_lane)
body:
[i][[Azur Lane]][/i]'s personification of the Japanese aircraft carrier [i]Katsuragi[/i], the third of the [i]Unryuu[/i]-class.
Character design by [[Izuru (Timbermetal)|]], voiced by [[Toda Megumi]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] with prominent [[twintails]] and [[blue eyes]]. Her outfit consists of [[shide]] that she uses to tie the twintails, an unorthodox [[blue dress]], white [[thighhighs]], black [[platform footwear]], [[see-through cape|see-through]] [[cape]], [[shimenawa]] belt, and an unorthodox see-through [[hakama]].

She uses a rig that is unorthodox of her standing as an aircraft carrier. Her rig prominently displays 12.7 cm DP twin mounts and 25 mm anti-air guns, reflective of the fact that she never fulfilled her intended carrier role. The rig does have two white banners, one on each side, that serve as her [[flight deck]]. As seen in the reference sheet, the red-colored marks are actually her [i]real-life camouflage pattern[/i].

In real life, she was completed late into the war and never received her air group, instead spending her career in Kure as an AA platform alongside her sister ship Amagi (of the Unryuu-class, not the battlecruiser [[Amagi (Azur Lane)|]]). Ultimately, she survived the war and served as a repatriation ship (the largest surviving ship Japan could field in that role) before being sold for scrap in 1946.

title: hai_chi_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the Imperial Chinese Navy protected cruiser [i]Hai Chi[/i] in [[Azur Lane]].

Historically, she and her sister ship [[Hai Tien (Azur Lane)|]] were the largest ships China had for several decades (compare their 4,300 tons while [[Ning Hai (Azur Lane)|]] had a displacement of 2,500 tons). She was originally commissioned in 1899 and served until 1937 when she was scuttled to slow down the Japanese advance down the Yangtze towards Wuhan.

In Azur Lane, she and her sister Hai Tien are reclassed as light cruisers to conform to existing gameplay ship types.

title: serval_landau
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]]. Voiced by [[Terakawa Aimi]] in Japanese. 

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] with a [[blue hair|blue]] [[gradient hair|gradient end]], and [[blue eyes]]. Her default outfit is a custom Silvermane Guard attire of an [[asymmetrical jacket|asymmetrical]] [[white jacket]] worn to her right, [[midriff]] [[black shirt]], [[choker]], black [[bridal gauntlets|bridal gauntlet]] on her left arm, [[blue skirt|blue]] [[pleated skirt]], [[black pantyhose]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]]. She uses a modified [[electric guitar]] as her main weapon.

She is the eldest daughter of the Landau family and a mechanic who runs the Neverwinter Workshop, a rock 'n' roll performance workshop in Belobog as a hobby. Older sister to [[Gepard Landau|Gepard]] and [[Lynx Landau|Lynx]]. 

h4. Costumes

* !post #7689976: Splash art
* !post #7732708: Make the World Clamor (signature Light Cone)

h4. Profile
[expand]
The free and rebellious eldest daughter of the Landau family. Once a close friend of Cocolia's, she is now a mechanic purely because she likes this job.

In the Everwinter-stricken Belobog, she opened a workshop called "Neverstop" that puts business on hold from time to time for outdoor rock 'n' roll performances.

And should anyone ask her about the workshop's profits... "This is just a hobby, dear. I'm not short on money."
[/expand]

title: gepard_landau
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]]. Voiced by [[Furukawa Makoto]] in Japanese.

He is portrayed with [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. His default outfit is a custom Silvermane Guard [[military uniform]] consisting of a [[black shirt]] worn under a [[fur-trimmed jacket|fur-trimmed]] [[white jacket]] with crystal [[armor]] pieces, single [[white gloves|white glove]] on his left hand, [[single gauntlet]] on his right hand, [[white pants]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[knee boots]]. 

He is the captain of the Silvermane Guards who belongs to the noble Landau family in Belobog, and is responsible for the city's defenses and maintains peace. Younger brother to [[Serval Landau|Serval]] and big brother to [[Lynx Landau|Lynx]]. 

h4. Appearance

* !post #7689981: Splash art
* !post #8768065: Moment of Victory (signature Light Cone)

h4. Profile
[expand]
An upright and noble captain of the Silvermane Guards who bears the name of the age-old Landau family.

In the blizzard-battered city of Belobog, defense is much more challenging than attack. Gepard and the Silvermane Guards he leads serve as the unbreakable iron defense of the Union in this hostile world.

Sometimes he is ridiculed by his sister and aide for his ever-scrupulous manner, but no one can deny that the people of Belobog have been able to maintain peace and comfort even with eternal winter on its doorstep...

With Gepard's protection, the city can carry on with its ordinary daily routine.
[/expand]

Her birthday is October 1st. Her seiyuu is [[Kurosawa Tomoyo]].

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/2/2b/GlacialMasterPortrait.jpg] has his black hair turning white, featuring black clothing with red decorations and a red sash.

body:

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/6/6b/Female_Paladin_Art.png] has her hair styled into a sidetail, with her outfit remaining mostly the same as her base class save for golden gauntlets, greaves and pauldrons, as well as black thighhighs.

As a "Savior":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/f/fb/SaviorPortrait.jpg], she wears additional armor; namely, a winged tiara and breastplate. Her hair is also now worn loose, and a pair of angel wings can be seen on her back. In the background is an avatar of "Carloso":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/b/b6/Carloso.jpg], the god the Knights serve.

title: idi_nahui
body:
An [[ukrainian text|Ukrainian]] (іди нахуй) and [[russian text|Russian]] (иди нахуй) vulgar expletive, usually translated as "go fuck yourself" or simply "fuck off". Can be rendered in various ways using the Latin alphabet, with the most common being 'idi nahui' (with 'idi nahuj' close behind).

Ukrainian "іді нахуй" is a part of transliteration of Russian "Русский военный корабль, иди нахуй" ("[[russo-ukrainian war|Russian warship, go fuck yourself]]"). This quote was used on a big amount of Ukrainian posters. One of those, with yellow text on blue background with big stylized "іді", later became a [[meme]] after being cropped to just "іді нахуй".

* !asset #23051790: Original poster
* !asset #23051811: Meme

title: kazama_souta
body:
Main/supportive character of [[Senpai ga Uzai Kouhai no Hanashi]], the deadpan snarker of the story. 

Initially was the "nameless male co-worker in the office other than Senpai" to crowd up the place, but he got his own character development later in the series. Often looks like he's lacking sleep sometimes - he does. Kazama is a man who knows "when to fold 'em" - butt in or leave at [i]just[/i] the right moment. Occasionally snarky just by presence alone. His seemingly expressionless face adds silliness in certain situations.
Has a hobby of making [[origami]] and is very skilled at it.

Is very in-sync with Sakurai to the point they're often seen as couple. Traits shared with her: whipping out his phone for making photos (usually Futaba's antics), messing with phone's photo apps. 

[spoiler]He essentially sees Sakurai as love interest and is her childhood friend.[/spoiler]

[i]Appearance:[/i] Average height, thin man. [[jitome|Flat half-open eyes]], black messy hair, constricted pupils. Usually expressionless.

Associated color: inconsistent "Shades of Azure":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shades_of_azure throughout series. Currently it's "True Blue.":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shades_of_azure#True_blue

title: ligne_claire
body:
[b]Ligne claire[/b] (French for "clear line") is an art style characterized by strong black [[outline|outlines]], [[flat color|flat colors]], and detailed backgrounds with little contrast between the subject and the background.

The style was popularized by Hergé, the creator of [[Tintin]]. In anime related art, the style was popularized by [[Cogecha]].

title: han_solo
body:
One of the main characters from [[Star Wars]]. He was played by actor [[Harrison Ford]] in the "Skywalker Saga" movies (specifically the original and sequel trilogies) and by "Alden Ehrenreich":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alden_Ehrenreich in his titular spin-off movie [[Solo: A Star Wars Story]].

[b]Han Solo[/b] is a galactic smuggler and former [[tie pilot|Imperial pilot]]. His [[spacecraft]] of choice is the [[Millennium Falcon]], which he won from [[Lando Calrissian]] in a high-stakes card game. [[Chewbacca]] is Solo's best friend and partner in crime.

He and Chewbacca were hired by [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Luke Skywalker]] on [[Tatooine]] to transport them to the planet Alderaan, but those plans soon went awry. Initially only aiding the [[Rebel Alliance (Star Wars)|Rebellion]] to pay off his debt to the crime lord [[Jabba the Hutt|Jabba]], Han shelved much of his cynicism, proved his heroism and became a Rebel leader.

[b]Major spoilers from [[star wars: the force awakens|Episode VII]] of Star Wars below.[/b]

[spoiler]After the defeat of the [[Galactic Empire (star wars)|]] following Episode VI, [[Star Wars: Return of the Jedi|Return of The Jedi]], he became the husband of [[princess leia|Leia]] and the father of [[Ben Solo]] a.k.a. [[Kylo Ren]]. In Episode VII, he confronts his son to try and turn him away from the Dark Side, but is killed by him.[/spoiler]

title: star_wars:_a_new_hope
body:
[b]Star Wars[/b] (retroactively retitled [b]Star Wars: Episode IV – A New Hope[/b]) is a 1977 American epic space opera [[science fiction]] film written and directed by [[George Lucas]], produced by Lucasfilm and distributed by [[20th century studios]].

The cast includes [[Mark Hamill]], [[Harrison Ford]], [[Carrie Fisher]], Peter Cushing, Alec Guinness, Anthony Daniels, Kenny Baker, Peter Mayhew, David Prowse, and [[James Earl Jones]].

Set a long time ago in a far away galaxy that is ruled by the tyrannical [[Galactic Empire (Star Wars)|]], the story focuses on a group of freedom fighters known as the [[Rebel Alliance (star Wars)|]], who aim to destroy the Empire's newest weapon, the [[Death Star]]. When Rebel leader [[Princess Leia|Princess Leia]] is apprehended by the Empire, [[Luke Skywalker]] acquires stolen architectural plans of the Death Star and sets out to rescue her while learning the ways of a metaphysical power known as "the Force" from [[Jedi]] Master [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]].

Star Wars was followed by [[The Star Wars Holiday Special]] in 1978, [[Star Wars: The Empire strikes back|The Empire Strikes Back]] in 1980 and [[Star Wars: return of The Jedi|Return of the Jedi]] in 1983, which concludes the original film trilogy.

title: ben_solo
body:
[b]Ben Solo[/b] is a character from the new sequel trilogy of [[Star Wars]] films. 

[spoiler]He is the son of [[Han Solo]] and [[Princess Leia]]. Ben trained to become a [[Jedi]] under his uncle [[Luke Skywalker]]'s tutelage. 

He was turned to the Dark Side of the Force by the evil Supreme Leader Snoke and became [[Kylo Ren]]. Ben killed other aspiring Jedi students and destroyed Luke's new Jedi Academy. After this Luke went into a self-imposed exile out of pity for his loss.[/spoiler]

Ben first appeared in the [[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]] film from 2015.

title: metro-goldwyn-mayer
body:
Iconic American film studio founded in 1924 by the merger of three separate studios (Metro Pictures, Goldwyn Pictures Corporation, and Louis B. Mayer Pictures) under one umbrella.  Also known by the initials "MGM."

The studio's famous and often-parodied logo is a roaring [[lion]] in a circle formed by strips of film, with the [[Latin text|Latin legend]] [i]Ars Gratia Artis[/i] ("Art for Art's Sake," MGM's motto) on top and a stylized [[comedy and tragedy masks|theatre mask]] below.

title: shado_(ufo)
body:
A fictional top-secret human organization from the [[ufo (1970 tv series)|UFO]] TV series from the early 1970s.

[b]S.H.A.D.O.[/b] ([b]S[/b]upreme [b]H[/b]eadquarters, [b]A[/b]lien [b]D[/b]efense [b]O[/b]rganization) is a hi-tech secret armed group created to defend the Earth from an [[alien]] invasion.

SHADO has a variety of advanced hardware and vehicles at its disposal to implement a layered defense of planet Earth. Early warnings of alien attack would come from SID, the Space Intruder Detector, a computerized tracking [[satellite]] that constantly scans for [[UFO]] incursions. 

The forward line of defense is Moonbase from which three [[Lunar Interceptor]] [[spacecraft]], carrying nuclear missiles, are launched. 

The second line of defense includes [[Skydiver]], a submarine mated with the submersible, undersea-launched [[Sky One]] interceptor aircraft, which attacks UFOs in Earth's atmosphere. 

The last line of defense are ground units including the heavy armed and armored, IFV-like [[SHADO Mobile]]s, fitted with caterpillar tracks.

Lt. [[Gay Ellis]] is a notable member of the group.

title: destroyer_(girls'_frontline)
body:
The [[Sangvis Ferri]] boss you fight in [[Girls' Frontline]]'s 5th Chapter, Model SP5NANO. Often appears alongside [[Dreamer (girls' frontline)|]], who treats her in a toxic fashion, yet simultaneously can't leave her be. During Deep Dive, Destroyer ends up getting uploaded into two bodies to fight off against their enemies - firstly into [[Cerberus (girls' frontline)|]], after being tricked into doing so, and then secondly into [[Gaia (girls' frontline)|]]. 

[quote][b]Enemy Bio:[/b]

An expert in blowing things up and disarming bombs who also possesses decent combat abilities. Occasionally teams up with Alchemist. She's usually haughty and sharp-tongued, but is actually a tsundere with a somewhat childish temper. She cries under pressure and is very sensitive about her height.

[b]Protocol Assimilation Bio:[/b]

An expert in detonation and disarming bombs who has some unique insight into the art of blowing things up. She is a sharp-tongued tsundere with a somewhat childish temper. She is also extremely competitive and enjoys trampling on the weak. To achieve her aims, she never skimps on firepower in battle.

Her voice actress is [[Takada Yuuki]].[/quote]

She's the third to receive a variant unit through Protocol Assimilation, in the form of [[Destroyer (Dashing Reindeer) (girls' frontline)|Dashing Reindeer]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #6043566: Default
* !post #6043567: 5* Protocol Assimilation
* !post #4992763: [[Gaia (girls' frontline)|]]
* !post #6043531: [[Destroyer (Dashing Reindeer) (girls' frontline)|Dashing Reindeer]]

h4. See also

* [[List of Girls' Frontline characters]]

h4. External links

* "IOP Wiki: Destroyer":[https://iopwiki.com/wiki/Destroyer]

body:

She is a "menreiki":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menreiki, a kind of youkai who was born from the legendary masks of "Hata no Kawakatsu":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hata_no_Kawakatsu. title: ags-30_(girls'_frontline)
body:
A Heavy Ordnance Corp, consisting of a trio of dolls manning a Russian [[AGS-30]] Grenade Launcher, in [[Girls' Frontline]].

All of them wear a distinctive [[digital camouflage]], [[military uniform]] underneath the [[load bearing vest]] with a white necktie. They have brown hair, but each of them has a distinctive hairstyle. They each also have hair decorations that looks like tripods as well. Their artist has also granted each a name, but these are artist headcanon until mentioned in-game.

The "loader" has twintails. She has brown eyes, wears red-trim glasses, black socks (as seen on her chibi sprite), and carries a red ID (with the name Alina).

The "spotter" has a side-ponytail. She has blue eyes, wears white thighhighs (as seen on her chibi sprite), and, unlike her other 2 "sisters", wears no glasses. She carries a blue ID (with the name Galina).

The "gunner" has a ponytail. She has red eyes, wears black thighhighs, glasses, and carries an orange ID (with the name Sonya).

h4. Appearance

* !post #5533626

h4. See also

* [[List of Girls' Frontline characters]]

h4. External links

title: steamed_bun
body:
A type of steamed, filled bun or bread-like [[dumpling]] originating in China, with regional varieties in many world cuisines. There are many variations in fillings ([[meat]] or vegetarian) and preparation (usually steamed).

In China, it is known as [i]baozi[/i]. It is derived from the traditional Chinese [[mantou]], a steamed bun without fillings (although regionally [i]mantou[/i] may refer to baozi as well).

In Japan, it is known as [i]manjuu[/i], the Japanese rendering of [i]mantou[/i]. A meat-filled [i]manjuu[/i] is a [i]nikuman[/i]; those referred to as [i]manjuu[/i] typically have a sweet filling. 

In [[Love Live! School Idol Project]], sweet [i]manjuu[/i] is the signature item of Homura Bakery, which [[Kosaka Honoka]]'s family owns and lives over. Good Smile Company, as a result, produced official Homura Bakery [i]manjuu[/i] in packs.

Other names for baozi include bao, bau, humbow, nunu, pow or pau.

h4. Examples

* !post #7182159
* !post #6434473

title: ibaraki_kasen
body:
"The One-Armed, Horned Sennin"

Introduced in the official comic [i]東方茨歌仙 ([[Touhou]] Ibarakasen) ～ [[Wild and Horned Hermit]][/i], serialized in Chara☆Mel Febri. An enigmatic [[pink hair|pink haired]], [[red eyes|red-eyed]] (or [[pink eyes|pink]]) "pilgrim" with her right [[bandaged arm|arm]] wrapped in [[bandages]] whose search for the "Kappa Arm" led her into the Hakurei Shrine. It is soon revealed that [[amputee|there is no arm inside her bandages]], which are instead filled with a mysterious magical smoke. She wears a [[tabard]] with a [[red rose]], a [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[white shirt]] and a [[green skirt]]. Her appetite for [[steamed bun]]s also has her frequently depicted with [[large breasts]] and/or [[eating]].

Due to the [[shackles|shackle]] on her left arm, her suspicious [[double bun]]s with [[bun cover]]s, and her title implying the existence of horns, there is rampant speculation among fans that Kasen is an [[oni]], specifically [[Ibaraki Douji_(mythology)|]], one of the Big Four. Some of Kasen's actions, such as her avoidance of [[Ibuki Suika]], also contribute to the speculation.

She is often accompanied by her pets: [[Koutei (touhou)|]] the dragon, [[Kume (touhou)|]] the giant eagle, [[Kanda (touhou)|]] the young eagle, [[Mukou (touhou)|]] the raijuu, and [[Houso (touhou)|]] the tiger.

Since both characters are hermits, Kasen is often associated with [[Kaku Seiga]], though usually on an antagonistic basis since Seiga is a "wicked hermit". 

[spoiler]Wild and Horned Hermit 35 revealed she is one of the Sages of [[Gensokyo]] alongside Yukari.[/spoiler]
[spoiler]Wild and Horned Hermit 49 would not only introduce her severed arm given semi-physical form, [[Ibaraki Douji's Arm]], but Kasen herself would become one with her arm and fully become an oni once more, revealing herself to be one of the Big Four, [[Ibaraki Douji (Touhou)|Ibaraki Douji]]. Also associated with [[Miyako Yoshika]] as the real Miyako No Yoshika wrote poems that Douji supposedly liked. [/spoiler]

Playable in Touhou 14.5 ~ Urban Legend in Limbo.

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Kasen Ibaraki":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Kasen_Ibaraki

title: dim_sum
body:
A style of Chinese cuisine prepared as small bite-sized portions of food served in small [[bamboo steamer]] baskets or on small [[plate]]s. Dim sum dishes are usually served with [[tea]], and together form a full tea brunch.

They can be cooked by steaming and frying, among other methods. A dim sum brunch includes various types of small [[steamed bun]]s, rice or wheat [[dumpling]]s, "rice noodle roll":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rice_noodle_roll], "chicken feet":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chicken_feet], "pork spare ribs":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spare_ribs], steamed green vegetables, roasted meats, congee and other soups, "glutinous rice dishes":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glutinous_rice] and [[sweets]] such as [[egg tart]], [[pudding]], [[sponge]], [[cake]]. The serving sizes are usually small and normally served as three or four pieces in one dish.

Use this tag when the dishes are displayed in brunch.

h4. Examples

title: kufei
body:
Character from [[Mahou Sensei Negima!]].

Seat 12 in [[Negi Springfield]]'s class. She is an extremely skilled Chinese martial artist who is very energetic and joyful. She is friends with [[Chao Lingshen]], and works with her and [[Yotsuba Satsuki]] at the Chao Bao Zi Chinese restaurant cart, where she also gorges on [[steamed bun|nikuman]].

It is a language barrier that holds her back from succeeding in class. But she can also be rather absent minded.

She has [[dark skin]] and [[green eyes]] with [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[blonde hair]] styled in a [[two side up]] hairstyle.

She is "Baka Yellow" in the [[mahora_baka_rangers|Baka Rangers]] study group.

title: sie_kensou
body:
The secondary character of [[Psycho Soldier]] and one of the characters in [[The King of Fighters]]. He is sometimes depicted carrying or eating a [[steamed bun]].

He claims himself to be [[Asamiya Athena]]'s love interest, only to get unlucky later on.

title: chao_lingshen
body:
Character from [[Mahou Sensei Negima!]].

Seat 19 in [[Negi Springfield]]'s class. She is in six Clubs as the Mahora Academy and is seen as a Happy-go-Lucky, very busy girl. She also runs the Chao Bao Zi Chinese restaurant cart with [[KuFei]] and [[Yotsuba Satsuki]], making her famous [[steamed bun|nikuman]]. And despite her busy schedule she still remains the Top ranking student in the school.

She is a master in Chinese martial arts.  Her origins are mysterious.

She has [[brown eyes]] and [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[black hair|black]]/[[brown hair]] in a [[double bun]], usually with in [[bun cover]]s and [[braid|braids]] by each bun.

Ambigous tag, previously used to refer to religious garments, most commonly the religious garments worn by Christian [[nun]]s. However, habit here broadly refers to the whole range of garments which exist for those involved in religious institutions, whether it be the clergy or religious brothers and sisters. These garments are typically tagged using the religious position in question. For those tags, please go to:

* [[nun]]

title: airship
body:
A type of fantasy [[aircraft]] or [[spacecraft]] from the [[fantasy]] or [[science fiction]] genres. Often, airships look similar to real [[ship]]s, except flying in the air or space through magical or fantastical means. For reference, the [[Palanquin ship]] and the [[Yamato (uchuu senkan yamato)|Space Battleship Yamato]] are the archtypical example of an airship.

This tag is not for real life blimps, but for fictional flying ships. For real life blimps, use [[dirigible]]. When in doubt, or when the vehicle exhibit characteristic of both vehicle types, apply both [[dirigible]] and [[airship]], or just use the [[aircraft]] tag.

[[Flying boat]]s are not to be confused with airships; they are a variation of [[seaplane]].

h4. Examples

title: yamato_(uchuu_senkan_yamato)
body:
[b]Space Battleship Yamato[/b] is the title [[spacecraft]]/[[airship]] from the anime series [[Uchuu Senkan Yamato]] and the [[Uchuu Senkan Yamato 2199]] remake. In real life it was designed by [[Matsumoto Leiji]] and [[Miyatake Kazutaka]].
 
In the series, the Space Battleship Yamato was created by the [i]Earth Defense Force[/i] in the late 22nd century. At this time our planet was under attack from an alien race, the [[Gamilas]], who were raining down [[meteor bomb]]s that evaporated Earth's oceans and rendered its surface uninhabitable. 

The new space warship was built inside the remains of the Japanese [[battleship]] [[Yamato (battleship)|]] (sunk during World War II in the sea near Okinawa) which was partially buried in what was now a dry seabed, thus concealing it from the view of the orbiting Gamilon vessels. The Space Battleship Yamato was finally launched on the year 2199.

In the American dub of the series, [[uchuu_senkan_yamato|Star Blazers]], the spaceship has the same origin but is named the [b]Argo[/b] (after the mythical ship "Argo" from [[greek_mythology|Jason and the Argonauts]]). In Spanish and Latin American countries its name was changed to [b]Intrepido[/b] ("Intrepid").

h4. See also

* [[Wave Motion Gun]]

title: doner_wrap
body:
A popular Eastern Mediterranean dish. It features [[doner kebab|meat cooked]] on a [[vertical rotisserie]], slowly turning and creating crispy, flavorful layers. The meat is shaved off as it cooks, and typically served with warm [[pita (food)|]] bread (or another type of flatbread) wrapped around it with fresh vegetables and a creamy sauce, like tzatziki.

Most well-known in the West by its Greek name, '[b]gyros[/b]', which is a translation of the Turkish 'döner', while in Turkey, it is known as 'dürüm kebab', referring to the rolled-up nature of the wrap; otherwise also referred to as 'shawarma', or even just 'kebab'.

h4. See also

* [[doner kebab]]
* [[doner sandwich]]
* [[shish kebab]]

h4. External links

* Wikipedia: "Gyros":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gyros] and "Dürüm":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/D%C3%BCr%C3%BCm]

title: doner_sandwich
body:
A popular dish originating from Turkey, popularized in the West by Turkish immigrants in Germany. It features [[doner kebab|meat cooked]] on a [[vertical rotisserie]], slowly turning and creating crispy, flavorful layers. The meat is shaved off as it cooks and typically served in a warm [[pita (food)|]] bread with fresh vegetables and a creamy sauce. Often just referred to as a 'döner', 'shawarma', or even just 'kebab'.

h4. See also

title: atelier_resleriana
body:
[b]Atelier Resleriana: Forgotten Alchemy and the Polar Night Liberator[/b] is the 25th mainline game in the [[atelier (series)|Atelier series]], developed by Akatsuki Games and published by Koei Tecmo. The story is penned by novelist Takahiro, with character designs by [[Umiu Geso]], [[tokki]], and [[NOCO_(adamas)|]]. Unlike previous mainline entries in the series, it is a free-to-play game with monetization centered around a gacha system.

It follows the story of the two titular protagonists: [[Resna Sternenlicht]], a novice alchemist who hopes to revive the concept of alchemy, and [[Valeria (atelier)|]], an adventurer who's lost most of her memories up to three years before the events of the game.

The game was released in Japan on September 23, 2023 for mobile devices, and on January 10, 2024 for PC through Steam. The global version was released worldwide on January 25, 2024 for both mobile devices and PC. The global version was "shut down":https://x.com/Resleriana_EN/status/1883818691709796796 on March 28, 2025.

The game heavily features characters from the wider Atelier series mysteriously transported into the world, known collectively as "wanderers".

title: chengdu_j-36

The [b]"Chengdu J-36"[/b] is a placeholder designation given to a Chinese prototype stealth [[fighter jet]] developed for the [[People's Liberation Army Air Force]]. The aircraft made its first public appearance on 26 December 2024, coinciding with the birthday of [[Mao Zedong]].

title: ore_no_imouto_ga_konna_ni_kawaii_wake_ga_nai
body:
[b]Ore no Imouto ga Konna ni Kawaii Wake ga Nai[/b] (俺の妹がこんなに可愛いわけがない, lit. [i]My Little Sister Can't Be This Cute[/i], abbrev. [i]OreImo[/i]) is a light novel series written by Fushimi Tsukasa, with illustrations by [[Kanzaki Hiro]]. Also adapted into a 2009 manga, with illustrations by [[Ikeda Sakura]], and a 2010 anime.

For years, 17-year-old [[Kousaka Kyousuke]] and his 14-year-old sister [[kousaka_kirino|Kirino]] rarely, if ever, talked to each other, until the day Kyousuke picks up a mahou-shoujo anime DVD case Kirino dropped, only to find out that it actually contains a little sister incest H-game. The ensuing chain of events finally force the siblings to have their first serious conversation in years.

h4. Characters
h6. Main
* [[Kousaka Kirino]]
* [[Kousaka Kyousuke]]

h6. Others
* [[Aragaki Ayase]]
* [[Gokou Ruri]]
* [[Ria Hagry]]
* [[Kousaka Daisuke]]
* [[Kousaka Yoshino]]
* [[Kurusu Kanako]]
* [[Makishima Saori]]
* [[Tamura Manami]]

h4. See also

* [[can't be this cute]]
* [[maschera ~datenshi-shita kemono no doukoku~]]
* [[hoshikuzu witch meruru]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Oreimo":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oreimo]
other_names: 俺の妹がこんなに可愛いわけがない

title: jing_yuan
body:
A [i][[Honkai: Star Rail]][/i] character. 

One of the seven generals of the Xianzhou Alliance's Cloud Knights and one of the Six Charioteers of the Luofu. Voiced by [[Ono Daisuke]] (JP) and [[Cy Yu|Alejandro Saab]] (EN).

He is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]] tied to a [[ponytail]], and [[yellow eyes]]. His outfit consists of a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[white shirt]] worn with [[shoulder armor]] and [[pauldrons]], [[black belt]], [[red pants]], [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]], and a [[red ribbon|red]] [[hair ribbon]] tying his ponytail.

h4. Appearance

* !post #7690439: Base art
* !post #8768157: Before Dawn (signature Light Cone)

h4. Profile
[expand]
Although his appearance may be one of indolence, the Cloud Knight general who commands the Xianzhou Luofu is more meticulous than seemingly meets the eye.

He does not consider saving a situation from the brink of disaster to be a show of wisdom, and is thus fastidious with routine affairs to avoid any potential problems.

Due to his careful management, the Xianzhou have enjoyed many years of peace, with Jing Yuan's seemingly lazy demeanor having earned him the moniker of "Dozing General."
[/expand]

title: battle_mage_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Female Mage_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]]. Also known as the Bellatrix or Astarte.

Her default appearance has high-set twintails, while her outfit consists of a short black jacket, red dress vest, black shorts, and jewelled gauntlets.

As an Astarte, her hair is generally longer and she wears a black and red one-piece with a long skirt and black shorts.

As a Neo Battle Mage, she wears fancier robes with gold trim and black thighhighs. Her older alter ego, an avatar of the goddess Teana, is reflected underneath her.

In all of her official appearances, she wields a spear of some variety, her weapon of choice.

h4. Appearance

* !asset #24660957: Default
* !asset #24660956: Astarte
* !asset #24660959: Neo Battle Mage

title: female_nen_master_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Female Fighter_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]]. Also known as the Blazing Flower or Nen Empress.

Her default appearance features an orange and white [[china dress]], with her hair done up in a [[half_updo|half updo]]. She wears jeweled gloves, which presumably helps her control and weaponize Nen.

As a Nen Empress, she wears a black [[china dress]] and [[black thighhighs]], with her hair now styled as a [[double bun]] and [[twintails]].

Her Neo Nen Master form goes back to a white [[china dress]], with the twintails now undone. Her thigh-highs include gold [[eastern_dragon|Eastern dragon]] wrappings.

title: demonic_lancer
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/3/30/Demon_Lancer_Full_Body.jpg] is a young man with dark purple hair and red eyes, wearing a gray jacket with fur trim, gray dress vest with white shirt, gray pants, and black gauntlets and greaves.

Subclasses:
* [[vanguard_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Vanguard]] (Revenant, Warlord)
* [[skirmisher (dungeon and fighter)|Skirmisher]] (Highlander, Durandal)
* [[impaler (dungeon and fighter)|Impaler]] (Abbadon, Erebus)
* [[dragoon_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Dragoon]] (Leviathan, Deimos)

title: impaler_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[demonic_lancer|Demonic Lancer]]. Also known as the Abbadon or Erebus.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/e/e2/Dark_Lancer_Art.png] has his hair parted down the middle, and a predominantly black version of his base class's outfit, minus the gauntlets. The right side of his face is pitch black, and his right eye has a slit pupil.

As an "Erebus":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/2/20/ErebusPortrait.png], he foregoes his black undershirt, revealing that the black discoloration on his face extends to parts of his chest and torso.

title: skirmisher_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[demonic_lancer|Demonic Lancer]]. Also known as the Highlander or Durandal.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/f/f2/SkirmisherPortrait.png] has his purple hair appear windswept, and he wears a short light gray jacket with a dark gray shirt and pants. He also comes equipped with gray pauldrons, gauntlets and greaves.

As a "Durandal":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/d/d9/DurandalPortrait.png], his appearance is still mostly the same, save for trading the jacket for a light gray cape and black fingerless gloves instead of gauntlets.

title: female_crusader_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[female_priest_(dungeon_and_fighter)|female Priest]]. Also known as the Evangelist or Seraphim.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/b/b2/Female_Crusader_Portrait.jpg] has much of her outfit recolored white and gold, with the addition of a small blue and white [[mitre]] on her head and a white top resembling a cape.

As a "Seraphim":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/6/69/Seraphim_Portrait.jpg], her black hair is now wavy, while her outfit is now predominantly white, gold, and blue, with the length of her robes going past her legs. Two pairs of gold angel wings are seen on her back.

h4. See also

* [[Male crusader (dungeon and fighter)|]]

title: male_priest_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/8/82/MalePriestPortrait.png] is a muscular man with brown short hair, sidelocks and beard. He's dressed in black and gold priest vestments, a white jacket and white pants, with a golden cross hanging around his neck.

He's voice actor is [[Kusunoki Taiten]] in Japanese version, [[Jo Gyuchun]] in Korean version and [[Liu Beichen]] in Chinese version.

Classes:
* [[male crusader (dungeon and fighter)|Crusader]] (Paladin, Saint)
* [[monk_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Monk]] (Templar, Justice)
* [[exorcist_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Exorcist]] (Hyperion, Draconid)
* [[avenger_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Avenger]] (Doom Guardian, Immortal)

title: male_crusader_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male priest (dungeon and fighter)|male Priest]]. Also known as the Paladin or Saint.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/6/6e/CrusaderPortrait.png] trades in his base class's outfit for red and white priest vestments with a white hooded cape. His hair has grown to shoulder length along with his beard.

As a "Saint":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/b/bc/Saint.png], his hair is cut short and his facial hair trimmed to a stubble, resembling his base class more. His clothes are now predominantly white, with plate armor appearing on his arms, left shoulder and legs. The golden hammer he wields is his signature weapon, the Jupiter Hammer.

As a "Neo Crusader":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/6/67/Neo-_Male_Crusader_Artwork.png], his appearance is a combination of his Crusader hairstyle and outfit and his Saint outfit's armor, along with a slight redesign of the Jupiter Hammer featuring more cross imagery.

h4. See also

* [[Female Crusader_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]]

title: agent_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/2/26/Gunblader_Portrait.png] is a bespectacled middle-aged man with dark skin and short gray hair. His outfit consists of a long white jacket, green dress shirt and vest, brown leather pistol holster and utility belt, black pants and brown boots.

Subclasses:
* [[secret agent (dungeon and fighter)|Secret Agent]] (Enforcer, Executioner)
* [[troubleshooter_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Troubleshooter]] (Wild Card, Renegade)
* [[hitman_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Hitman]] (Big Boss, Godfather)
* [[specialist_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Specialist]] (Core Master, Pathfinder)

title: secret_agent_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Agent (dungeon and fighter)|]]. Also known as the Enforcer or Executioner.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/7/71/Agent_Concept_Art.png] has his hair slicked back, wearing a green military vest with a white long-sleeved undershirt, various leather pistol and magazine holsters, black pants, black boots and black gloves.

As an "Executioner":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/a/a1/Requiem_Portrait.png], his undershirt is now black and he also wears a dark gray trenchcoat.

title: specialist_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[agent (dungeon and fighter)|Agent]]. Also known as the Core Master or Pathfinder.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/0/0b/Specialist_Full_Body_Art.png] features messy, swept back hair, held back by a pair of blue goggles on his head. He wears a shorter beige coat with several pockets and blue lights on its shoulders, with similar blue lights on his brown leather belt; he otherwise appears the same as his base class.

As a "Pathfinder":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/0/08/Pathfinder_Portrait.png], he loses the goggles and leaves his messy hair down. He now wears a longer white coat and much of the remainder of his outfit has been recolored blue.

title: hitman_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[agent (dungeon and fighter)|Agent]]. Also known as the Big Boss or Godfather.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/c/ca/Hitman_Full_Body_Art.png] has a look that's almost exactly the same as his base class, with the only notable difference being that his hair is parted to the left.

As a "Godfather":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/b/b0/Godfather_Portrait.png], his hair is parted in the opposite direction and he sports an olive green coat and black dress vest. In the background, two of his fellow Agents - one in a white coat and another in black - are seen firing at off-screen enemies.

title: troubleshooter_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[agent (dungeon and fighter)|Agent]]. Also known as the Wild Card or Renegade.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/1/18/Trouble_Shooter_Concept_Art.png] gives him shoulder-length hair and [[pince-nez]] sunglasses. He trades in his white coat for a beige poncho concealing a variety of grenades underneath.

As a "Renegade":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/5/5d/Untouchable_Portrait.png], his hair has been styled into a thin ponytail, his poncho has been recolored dark gray, and his glasses were removed. He also sports a long, white cape.

title: male_launcher_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male gunner (dungeon and fighter)|Gunner]]. Also known as the Wrecking Ball or Destroyer.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/3/3b/Male_LauncherPortrait.png] is similar to his base class, with the only differences being that his right sleeve is hanging off his shoulder and a leather shoulder pad present on his left shoulder. He wields a gatling gun, being one of his sub-weapon skills.

As a "Destroyer":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/5/58/Dnf_season_4_destroyer_by_toonegeminielf-d7nu8f5.png], he wears a black military outfit with a sleeveless top and magazine harness, dual wielding a pair of laser cannons.

His "Neo Launcher":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/2/24/Neo-_Male_Launcher_Artwork.png] appearance gives him a sleeved red top, and is now wielding a railgun. In the background is a satellite cannon, one of the new skills he gains as a Neo Launcher.

title: male_mechanic_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male gunner (dungeon and fighter)|Gunner]]. Also known as the Machinist or Prime.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/b/b9/MechanicPortrait.png] is similar to his base class, with the purple trenchcoat's top being undone and left hanging off of his waist. Accompanying him are several small robots, which he uses in combat.

As a "Prime":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/1/1f/Dnf_season_4_prime_by_toonegeminielf-d7nu8xr.png], he now has curled hair and no longer has his purple trenchcoat, instead wearing a red hooded vest. He's also seen wielding a submachine gun, his class's weapon of choice.

His "Neo Mechanic":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/9/92/Neo-_Male_Mechanic_Artwork.png] appearance is generally the same as his Prime outfit, now wearing glasses and a long red jacket. Green goggles hang around his neck.

title: male_ranger_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male gunner (dungeon and fighter)|Gunner]]. Also known as the Raven or Desperado.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/d/d6/MaleRangerPortrait.png] features mostly the same clothing as his base class with the addition of a black cowboy hat. He wields the white-handled revolvers seen in his base class's art, with an upper body harness holstering two more revolvers.

As a "Raven":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/3/36/Dnf_season_4_raven_by_toonegeminielf-d7nu67r.png], his clothing is now black with red trimmings, swapping his old trenchcoat for an unzipped black one. Feathers from his namesake trail behind him.

His appearance as a "Neo Ranger":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/f/f8/Neo-_Male_Ranger_Artwork.png] is mostly similar to his Raven outfit, with his jacket now being zipped and parts of his clothing in tatters, presumably due to gunfire. His revolvers feature short-bladed bayonets on them, much like his [[female_ranger_(dungeon_and_fighter)|female counterpart]].

title: elementalist_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Female Mage_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]]. Also known as the Archmage or Overmind.

Her default appearance has her side tail rearranged as a ponytail, with more natural bangs held by a pair of hair clips. She wears robes with white sleeves, red torso and black bottom, with a white skirt and black thighhighs.

As an Overmind, her hair has been arranged into twintails. The colors on her top are reversed and she's now wearing white thighhighs. She also wears a black headband with gold decorations on it.

As a Neo Elementalist, her hair is almost the length of her body and has a slight orange tinge at its ends. She wears robes that are now predominantly white with gold trim and a red skirt.

h4. Appearance

* !asset #24660697: Default
* !asset #24660698: Overmind
* !asset #24660699: Neo Elementalist
